oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Gov. Frank G. Clement (1920-1969), Democratic governor of Tennessee from 1953-1959 and again from 1963-1967.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Clement's administration saw the beginning of the 4-year term for governors, free textbooks in public schools, and the creation of the TN Mental Health Department.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Governors
